lyTime":"2019-09-02T11:59:08.000Z","msg":"831=721<br />\n推"},{"pid":"304825d49118998469bde0c4e41c8cd2f2d484c3","tid":1531850,"uid":226972,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-02T12:01:01.000Z","msg":"For foreigners of LIHKG, this is a brief summary of both of the existing parties/stakeholders of the Anti-extradition protest period. The post will only introduce the two main opposing parties of the incident, stated below.<br />\n<br />\nThe communists, or the government supporters (Especially Chinese):<br />\n<br />\nThe communists are wicked beings, always thinking of new ways to trick Hong Kong into a vulnerable position, solely for the reason of getting the properties and the economy advantage that Hong Kong holds, since the PRC (People's Republic of China) itself is experiencing a national bankruptcy, and not having the bravery to face the horrible fate of their country, they went to seek our properties ambitiously and recklessly by using the 'Extradition law' as an excuse for maintaining its wellbeing and at the same time, gain more and more access and control of Hong Kong, hoping to shorten the time for 'unification'. Unfortunately for China, Hong Kong has already been different from China for decades as the UK colonized us and western culture, and high-end culture got into Hong Kong while the Chinese maintain its low-end, agricultural culture, and this has already indicated that 'unification' (or simply conquering Hong Kong) would be unlikely due to the massive cultural gaps between China and Hong Kong. Throughout the waves and waves of protests, the communists recklessly beat up the young, and also turning lies into truths blatantly and shamelessly, ruining the future generation and the lights of Hong Kong&rsquo;s future.<br />\n<br />\nThe Activists/Protesters <br />\n<br />\nThe protestors are a group of people mainly made up of teenagers. They are people who fight for the freedom of Hong Kong from the wrath of the PRC, and are a bunch of enthusiastic activists that know the truth and are willing to fight for democracy, and fight for their own place and their home. Their sacrificial acts, blood that they shed, and the hard work they have done should be highly appreciated as one of the last, but strong struggle of a critically injured territory. No matter how long the sinister government ignores their needs or requests, they will keep on fighting, never giving up no matter how weary the fight can get. Despite the brutal acts from their opposing parties, like the police or the China supporters, they continue on their journey to fight for democracy with perseverance and a battling spirit.<br />\n<br />\nI understand there are also other stakeholders that take an important part in the anti-extradition period, like the police and the government, but these are the two main opposing parties of the incidents and it is decided that introducing these main parties above would be more of an appropriate choice. Thank you for reading the post, and please consider sharing the post to your family and friends, so to spread and defend the democracy and rights we, as Hongkongers deserve rightly."},{"pid":"2043bd1a429a3c8dc3b9c4f9c8ad9d9f37cd879c","tid":1531850,"uid":59684,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-02T12:46:12.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/bang.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"b7ca008630464591ad2a0ed7fa7dc4ec7e44597a","tid":1531850,"uid":59684,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-02T12:46:36.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/bomb.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"80e8562b4f3916c5b484b2b44140ad1cad90d353","tid":1531850,"uid":25825,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-02T12:51:26.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"9de3926b710b0fad4fb4c5704ccb3b9c94fc7897","tid":1531850,"uid":257319,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-